# v2.1.18 (CO-6): Test directories tracked policy.
#
# History: Pre-v2.1.18 used `test/` + `tests/*` blanket ignore with explicit
# `!test/contract/` etc. negate patterns. Git's directory traversal halts at
# the first ignored directory boundary — so deep negates like `!test/foo/**`
# did NOT actually re-include files. This led to several CI-referenced test
# files (l2-hook-attribution, l3-mcp-runtime, bkit-full-system, bkit-deep-
# system, 29 tests/qa/*.test.js) silently staying untracked across multiple
# v2.1.14~v2.1.16 releases, only surfacing when CI ran them and reported
# `Cannot find module`.
#
# v2.1.18 new policy: production test directories are tracked by default.
# Only explicit local/temporary patterns are ignored. New `.test.js` files
# are automatically picked up by `git status` — no `git add -f` needed.
#
# See docs/06-guide/test-file-tracking-policy.guide.md.
test-scripts/
test/contract/baseline/tmp/
test/contract/baseline/.tmp/
test/local/
test/manual-only/
tests/local/
tests/manual-only/

# Obsidian - Root level (personal settings, not for sharing)
.obsidian/

# Obsidian - bkit-system (keep graph.json and core-plugins.json for documentation)
bkit-system/.obsidian/app.json
bkit-system/.obsidian/appearance.json
bkit-system/.obsidian/workspace.json
bkit-system/.obsidian/plugins/

# bkit runtime state (agent-state.json)
.bkit/

# Session history (local Claude Code history hooks; machine-local, not for repo)
.remember/

# Working directory — session notes, scratch, and local archives (machine-local)
work/

# Local Claude Code settings (plugin elements are at root level)
.claude/
# v2.1.11: project-level CLAUDE.md is part of the plugin contract
# (referenced by test/contract/invocation-inventory.test.js)
!.claude/CLAUDE.md

# Docs folder (too large for plugin distribution)
docs/.pdca-snapshots/
docs/archive/
docs/bkit-Best-Practice.pdf

# Internal skills/commands (company-only, not for public repo)
skills/github-integration/
commands/github-stats.md

# Jest config — references a non-existent test-scripts/ dir; the project's tests
# run via `node` (see .github/workflows/contract-check.yml), not Jest. Kept
# locally for ad-hoc node-style tests; excluded from the repo. Untracked via
# `git rm --cached jest.config.js` (file retained on disk).
jest.config.js
